TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chen, Tao
AU  - Zhang, Li
AU  - Zhu, Qifei
T1  - Dual Ownership and Risk-Taking Incentives in Managerial Compensation*
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfad007
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 27
IS  - 5
SP  - 1823
EP  - 1857
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This article studies how the three-way interaction among shareholders, creditors, and managers shapes firms’ executive compensation. Firms with a higher ownership share by “dual holders”—institutional investors that simultaneously hold equity and bond of the company—adopt a less risk-inducing compensation structure: less stock options and more inside debt. Exploiting financial institution mergers that increase or decrease dual ownership for portfolio companies, we identify a causal link between dual ownership and CEO compensation policies. Mutual fund proxy voting data suggest that shareholder voting is an important channel for dual holders to implement less convex contracts.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfad007
ER  - 



